    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "* 304\nN4804C\nVeltatS\nDELTA",
      "DELTA-C \u0026 S AIR LINES\nConvair 340\nDelta Air Lines received its first Convair 340 in December.\n1952. Carrying 44 passengers in an air conditioned, pres-\nsurized cabin, the Convairliner cruised at 250 MPH, and\nbrought a new level of comfort and service to the airline's\nshorter routes. Delta Air Lines absorbed Chicago \u0026 Southern\nAir Lines by merger on May 1, 1953, and for approximately\ntwo years thereafter operated as Delta - C \u0026 S Air Lines,\nalthough their corporate name remained Delta Air Lines,\nInc. Early in 1970 Delta retired its last Convair, becoming\nin all-jet airline.\nPublished by Aviation World, Inc., P.O. Box 188, Bethel, Conn. 06801 U.S.A.\nPhoto courtesy Delta Air Lines\nN4804C c/n 51\nC-013,\n6980 -D\npost card\n2015.166.0616"
    ],
